  $( The power class of the union of two classes equals the union of their
     power classes, iff one class is a subclass of the other.  Part of Exercise
     7(b) of [Enderton] p. 28. $)
  pwun $p |- ( ( A C_ B \/ B C_ A ) <->
             ~P ( A u. B ) = ( ~P A u. ~P B ) ) $=
